OL,3,C'Migraine can be lonely and
OL,4,Cdebilitating but new drug gives me
OL,5,Chope'
OL,7,FHe added: "Throughout, obviously the
OL,8,Fnumber of years, I've tried a number
OL,9,Fof different things the GP has offered
OL,10,Fand you almost feel like a bit like a
OL,11,Flab rat in terms of being able to
OL,12,Funderstand how it would work for you
OL,13,Fto the point where, late twenties, I
OL,14,Fjust gave up in terms of medication."
OL,16,FAbout 10 million adults in the UK are
OL,17,Fthought to have experienced or live
OL,18,Fwith migraine, with about one in five
OL,19,Fwoman and one in twelve men affected.
