OL,4,Cdebilitating but new drug gives me
OL,5,Chope'
OL,7,FRob Music, from the Migraine Trust,
OL,8,Fsaid: "For too many years, migraine
OL,9,Fhas been very much left to the one
OL,10,Fside and not taken seriously.
OL,12,F"We are seeing changes now. That's
OL,13,Fgreat. So great there's a new
OL,14,Ftreatment but it's only great if the
OL,15,Fpeople who need it, who deserve it can
OL,16,Faccess it as soon as they possibly can
OL,17,Fand that's the bit that must change."
OL,19,FLast year, the Bishop Auckland MP
OL,20,FDehenna Davison
